Package processing

Class Author

java.lang.Object
processing.Author
public class Author extends Object
Represents the author of a type of work represented by a first and last name. The author can also have an optional identification number/string.
Since:
1.0

  • Constructor Details

    • Author

      public Author(@NonNull @NonNull String firstname, @NonNull @NonNull String lastname, String id)
      Creates a new author by specifying the first and last name separately. Note that the parameters are taken "as is".
      Parameters:
      firstname - - the first name of the string as a whole string. For example: "John"
      lastname - - the last name of the string as a whole string. For example: "Doe"
      id - - the ID of the author as a whole string if it exists, or null if it does not exist

    • Author

      public Author(@NonNull @NonNull String name, String id)
      Creates a new author by specifying the name as a whole string. In that case, all characters until the first white space character are interpreted as the first name, and all characters after it are interpreted as the last name. If the first or last names are blank, the compilation fails with an exception
      Parameters:
      name - - the name of the assessor as a whole string. For example: "John Doe"
      id - - the role of the assessor as a whole string if it exists, or null if it does not exist
